<div class="headCo">

# <span>Iterators and Infinite Loops</span>

<div class="headCo_co">

<div>

<div class="infobloc">

<div class="txt">

If no iterator is used, or if an iterator is used the wrong way, OMLoop
gets stuck and potentially goes on forever.

</div>

</div>

<div class="part">

## <span>Example : Generating Numbers</span>

<div class="part_co">

<div class="infobloc">

<div class="txtRes">

<table>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%" />
<col style="width: 50%" />
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td><div class="dk_txtRes_txt txt">
<p>We want to generate four random numbers between 1 and 4.</p>
<p>Instead of using forloop to define the number of steps of the iteration, we have used repeat-n : OMLoop will never end and generate <strong>four random numbers</strong> an infinite number of times...</p>
</div></td>
<td><div class="caption">
<div class="caption_co">
<img src="../res/infiniteloop.png" width="158" height="192" alt="infiniteloop.png" />
</div>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</div>

<div class="part">

## <span>Abort Procedures</span>

<div class="part_co">

<div class="infobloc">

<div class="infobloc_ti">

<span>Abort Dialogue Window</span>

</div>

<div class="txtRes">

<table>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%" />
<col style="width: 50%" />
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td><div class="caption">
<div class="caption_co">
<img src="../res/ABORT.png" width="275" height="130" alt="ABORT.png" />
</div>
</div></td>
<td><div class="dk_txtRes_txt txt">
<p>An abort dialogue window pops up after a while (by default, 500 000 loops). To stop the iteration, choose <code class="textButton_tl">Abort</code>, unless you have planned a very long iteration...</p>
</div></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

</div>

</div>

<div class="infobloc">

<div class="infobloc_ti">

<span>Abort Command</span>

</div>

<div class="txt">

Type `Cmd` + `SHIFT` + `a` to abort the ongoing calculation.

</div>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</div>

</div>

